      • getPluginGoalName

        public abstract String getPluginGoalName()
        The Goal Name of the Plugin being tested.

        Used to look for <configuration> section in the plugin-config.xml that will be used to configure the mojo from.

        Returns:
        the string name of the goal. (eg "version-update", "dex", etc...)

      • createMojo

        protected T createMojo(String resourceProject)
                                            throws Exception
        Copy the project specified into a temporary testing directory. Create the MavenProject and ManifestUpdateMojo, configure it from the plugin-config.xml and return the created Mojo.

        Note: only configuration entries supplied in the plugin-config.xml are presently configured in the mojo returned. That means and 'default-value' settings are not automatically injected by this testing framework (or plexus underneath that is suppling this functionality)

        Parameters:
        resourceProject - the name of the goal to look for in the plugin-config.xml that the configuration will be pulled from.
        resourceProject - the resourceProject path (in src/test/resources) to find the example/test project.
        Returns:
        the created mojo (unexecuted)
        Throws:
        Exception - if there was a problem creating the mojo.

      • getProjectDir

        Get the project directory used for this mojo.
        Parameters:
        mojo - the mojo to query.
        Returns:
        the project directory.
        Throws:
        IllegalAccessException - if unable to get the project directory.
